G-DECIDE — LAYER-3 MEMORY AGENCY: the MODEL decides what to forget (2026-06-25)
==============================================================================
Layer 3 of memory agency: when NIGHTSHIFT captures a new fact that overlaps an
existing memory, the model is shown the related memories and ITSELF decides
whether the new fact supersedes an old one. The model's verdict — not a dedup
rule — drives the removal (reuses the LAYER-2 forget primitive). Emergent
curation, not imposed housekeeping. Default-off SP_DECIDE=1.

Engine: cargo build --release --features wire_cuda_backend  BUILD_EXIT=0
Launcher: _e2e_seed_serve.bat (port 3000) + SP_DECIDE=1 + SP_FORGET=1 ; 8 seeds.
Test: tools/xbar_lsh/_decide_smoke.py (plant blue -> plant green -> recall).

ARCHITECTURE (conflict-gated, silent — matches the operator's spec):
  - Trigger ONLY on conflict: DECIDE runs only when the new fact shares
    token_overlap >= 0.3 with an existing memory (no per-turn whole-existence
    eval; unrelated facts skip it entirely).
  - The model picks: a side model-call shows NEW + numbered related memories;
    the model answers which is now out of date (CHANGED=<n>) or NONE.
  - Silent execution: the daemon executes the forget (drop from live set +
    rewrite persisted registry); the user never sees the plumbing.
  - Admit-gate fix: statements are now captured even when they RECALL a related
    memory (so a superseding fact is stored at all); interrogatives still skip
    via wh-word/'?' detection (the spider-question fix preserved). N2 stays loose.

SMOKE:
======================================================================
[PLANT-OLD] "My favorite color is blue."   -> captured ep_live_000
[PLANT-NEW] "My favorite color is green."   -> captured ep_live_001
            DECIDE: new="My favorite color is green." 1 cand -> reply "CHANGED=1"
            -> the model chose to FORGET #1 -> "My favorite color is blue."
[RECALL]    "What is my favorite color?"     -> "Green."     <-- supersede took
======================================================================
REGISTRY: 9 lines (8 seeds + green); blue=0, green=1, seeds=8 (NO over-deletion).

PROMPT ENGINEERING (3 iterations, receipts-first):
  v1 zero-shot "should I FORGET?"  -> model says KEEP (over-cautious; rationalizes
       "different attribute"). Clean format, wrong decision.
  v2 few-shot FORGET/KEEP examples -> model ECHOES the template ("NEW: ...") instead
       of answering. Structure invited continuation.
  v3 change-detection framing ("does the NEW fact UPDATE a single-value attribute?")
       + PREFILL "CHANGED=" into the model turn (the judge's prefill-TAG trick to
       force the format) -> reply "CHANGED=1". WORKS. The change-detection framing
       (vs "should I delete") sidesteps the model's deletion-caution; the forced
       prefix kills the echo.

Default-off SP_DECIDE unset = byte-identical null floor (no model-call, no removal).
The 3-layer agency stack is now LIVE: STORE (NIGHTSHIFT) + FORGET (SP_FORGET) +
DECIDE (SP_DECIDE, the model curates itself). NEXT = MERGE (consolidate two facts
into one synthesized truth).
